title: EastEnders favourite Barry Evans becomes a HUMAN CANNONBALL in new role on Casualty
text:
BARRY'S BULLET EastEnders favourite Barry Evans becomes a HUMAN CANNONBALL in new role on Casualty 
Eager soap fans took to Twitter to share their delight the TV star was back on-screen By BETH ALLCOCK, Showbiz Reporter 4th February 2017, 10:12 pm Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Comments EASTENDERSâ€™ bumbling Barry Evans shot back onto screens on Saturday as he was fired from a cannon in an explosive episode of Casualty. 
Eagle-eyed Shaun Williamson fans took to Twitter in delight as they spotted their favourite TV star in his new role as adventure-seeking Terry. He became a human cannonball at the start of the show BBC Actor Shaun Williamson was loved by fans for his role in EastEnders EastEnders favourite Barry gets shot out of a cannon in Casualty 
At the start of Saturday night's episode he was seen clambering into the bright blue device clad in a white helmet 
His head could be seen peeking out from the hole in the top before he was fired off and landed in an ungraceful heap on the floor. 
Later he muttered: "I need to fly - that's who I am." 7 He blast off from the huge blue device in an attempt to fly 
After witnessing their soap favourite in the bizarre stunt excited viewers took to social media in their droves, with one commenting: "Turned on Casualty for the first time in forever, to see Barry from Eastenders be fired out a cannon. This is incredible." 
Another surmised: "I always wondered what was missing from my life. Turns out it was seeing Barry from Eastenders being shot out of a cannon," while one posted: "Barry fired from a canon! Casualty's got very weird." 
Another quipped: "Barry from Eastenders on # Casualty as a human cannonball, this can only end badly," while one posted their shock and said: "Barry from eastenders is currently on casualty as a human cannonball." 
One mused: "Poor Barry # casualty off to fly one more time." Turned on Casualty for the first time in forever, to see Barry from Eastenders be fired out a cannon. This is incredible.

One commented: "Poor Barry - life never gets any better does it?" 
Another wrote: "First Barry gets pushed down a hill by Jannine, now the poor sods got lung cancer," while a third added: "Tonight's Casualty. "Look it's Barry from EastEnders". Yet things didn't really look brighter in Shaun's new role as thrill-seeker Tez. 
He was initially suspected to have a seizure before the nurse then revealed it was more serious. 
He was forced to tell his mate - who fired off the cannon - he had lung cancer which had spread to the brain, and was the cause of the seizures.
